Arsenal to Bid $32 Million for Liverpool's Pepe Reina, Star Says: Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-02-28T09:30:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/arsenal-to-bid-32-million-for-liverpool-s-pepe-reina-star-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Arsenal for Reina  Arsenal plans to sign Liverpool goalkeeperPepe Reina for
20 million pounds ($32.2 million) at the end of the season, the
 Daily Star  reported.  The 28-year-old wants to play Champions League soccer in
the next campaign, and there is no chance of that at Anfield,
the Star said.  Rooney Ruling    Wayne Rooney  could face a three-match ban after he appeared
to elbow Wigan’s James McCarthy in the back of the head, the
 Daily Express  reported.  Referee Mark Clattenburg’s account of the clash in his
match report will determine whether Rooney is sanctioned, the
Express said.  Easiest Goal  Birmingham striker Obafemi Martins said his winning goal in
yesterday’s League Cup final victory against Arsenal is the
easiest he has scored,  the Sun  reported.  The Nigerian hit in a tap-in after 89 minutes to down
Arsenal 2-1 at Wembley Stadium.  Chelsea Refusal  Newcastle’s Cheik Tiote rejected a move to Chelsea on the
last day of the January transfer window partly because  London  is
too busy, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The 24-year-old Ivory Coast midfielder feels settled in
northeast  England  and recently signed a 6 1/2-year contract, the
Mail said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Duff in Madrid at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Christopher Elser  at 
 celser@bloomberg.net . 